chunk_content: T The CD4 result returned disaggregate for restarting or reinitiating on ART allows for targeted R E programming directed at reducing mortality from advanced HIV disease. Same day ART initiation A should not be delayed due to pending CD4 results. If CD4 results are pending longer than 1 week, T they should report patient under “Unknown CD4 result” disaggregate. For smaller facilities without M access to molecular testing, there will be majority of results in Unknown CD4 disaggregate. E N How to collect: When a patient experiences interruption in treatment (i.e., more than 28 days since their most recent T expected clinical contact), the clinic or other related staff should attempt to reach and reengage the patient as soon as possible. A patient is counted under TX_RTT in the reporting period in which the patient returns to treatment and restarts ARVs.
